				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Practical effect of CS3?<a name="54361"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 29 04 6:48 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I've read in a number of threads that Combat Stability doesn't just mitigate a percentage of all incoming damage, but actually has a chance to work, then mitigates a percentage, and so only reduces the average hit.
<br />

<br />
This is very much counter to the description of the AA, but that's beside the point.  My question is: what would be the practical effect of CS3?  Would it reduce overall damage by about 10%?  Even the roughest back-of-an-envelope calculations would be appreciated.
<br />

<br />
If it isn't that good, I'd have to say that getting Combat Agiligy 3 and LR5 would be the best option before even touching CS, if you want the most bang for your AA buck.
<br />

<br />
Cheers,</span></td>
