				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Practical effect of CS3?<a name="54536"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 30 04 9:06 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Even with CS3/ID5, mobs can still hit you for max damage. CS affects the DI multiplier from what I can glean from the Steel Warrior, but I'm not 100% sure how. 
<br />

<br />
From what I understand, every time a mob swings at you, you get a chance to avoid the hit entirely, and if it connects, you get a chance to mitigate the hit, which sets the DI multiplier to zero. CS/ID affects the mitigation chance, CA/LR affects the avoidance chance. Otherwise mob damage is DB + xDI where x is an integer between 1 and 20.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
