				<td colspan="2"><span>My reasoning on taking CA / LR over CS is that my usual death sequence starts with a successful bash and then goes downhill from there very quickly.  Doesn't matter whether you're swarm-kiting and something warped on you or you go around a blind corner in an LDoN and four mobs jump you.   Better to dodge a bash altogether than have it mitigated down by 5%.  
<br />

<br />
I also wonder if the reason warriors find CS better than CA really applies to bards.  Warriors are about minimizing damaging in a steady and predictable way so that healers can keep up on raids.  CA is definitely not predictable.  </span></td>
