				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Practical effect of CS3?<a name="55065"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 4 04 9:27 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The official in-game description for CS is:
<br />

<br />
&quot;This ability increases melee damage mitigation by 2/5/10%&quot;
<br />

<br />
That's a pretty cut-and-dry description.  Going by that, one would get the crazy idea that the ability would increase your melee damage mitigation.  Meaning that if you and a druid both took hits for max damage, you would always take less damage than the druid.
<br />

<br />
If it doesn't work like that, then the description should read something like:
<br />

<br />
&quot;This ability gives you a chance to mitigate melee damage by an additional 2/5/10%&quot;
<br />

<br />
I really think its unfortunate for all of us that discussions like this even have to take place.  We shouldn't have to decipher, test and compare results to understand in-game &quot;descriptions&quot; of abilities.
<br />

<br />
PS.  Maybe Tremelo can pass this along through his channels, not just for bards, but for all players.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
